14 commercial leases shall provide for fair market value throughout the
15 term of the lease. Such term limitations shall not apply to
16 investment real estate as defined in subsection D of Section 1013 of
17 this title. All investment real estate leases shall provide for
18 fair market value throughout the term of the lease.
19 Agricultural leases of trust property shall be limited to a
20 maximum of five (5) years and shall be by public bidding at not less
21 than fair market value.
22 The granting of any interest in trust property at less than fair
23 market value or not in compliance with this section is void.
